meta {
  name: Mass-Assign 05 Cleanup Decoy Survey
  type: http
  seq: 6
}

delete {
  url: {{host}}/v1/surveys/sec_attacker_decoy
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

docs {
  Best-effort cleanup. createFromData inserts a fresh row with the
  attacker-supplied name (here "sec_attacker_decoy") before assignProperties
  redirects $study->id to the victim. Pre-fix, that fresh row orphans —
  it's owned by the attacker but has no run-unit linkage. Post-fix the
  row may or may not exist depending on which branch of createFromData
  fired; either way we attempt the DELETE.
}
